-- Argentine Stocks: Ledesma, Petroleo Brasileiro and YPF Advance
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2011-12-22T20:32:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-22/argentine-stocks-ledesma-petroleo-brasileiro-and-ypf-advance.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the close in Buenos
Aires.  The  Merval (MERVAL)  Index rose 0.6 percent to 2,456.34.  Ledesma SAAI (LEDE)   advanced 5.3 percent to 7.18 pesos.
The Argentine sugar producer has gained 19 percent in the last
three days as it may be included in the benchmark Merval index
in 2012, according to a simulation published Dec. 19 by the
index’s developer, Instituto Argentino de Mercado de Capitales.  Petroleo Brasileiro SA (PETR4)   rose 1.7 percent to 59.5
pesos. Brazil’s state-controlled oil company followed crude
prices higher. Petrobras also said in a filing it plans to
invest 8.26 billion reais ($4.45 billion) in 2012 to modernize
refining operations.  YPF SA (YPFD AF) rose 0.6 percent to 161 pesos.  Argentina ’s
largest oil company had its rating increased to “outperform”
from “hold” by BBVA Bancomer SA analyst Jean-Baptiste Bruny,
according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
